Key Match Events: Wayne Parnell was out for a duck, caught by Scott Edwards and bowled by Brandon Glover.
Colin Ackermann was named man-of-the-match for his unbeaten 41.
Brandon Glover took 3 wickets for 9 runs in two overs.
Quinton de Kock and Temba Bavuma were out inside six overs with the score on 39.
Rilee Rossouw was dismissed after a 19-ball 25.
Fred Klaassen took the wicket of Quinton de Kock.
Paul van Meekeren bowled Temba Bavuma for 20.
Brandon Glover dismissed David Miller for 17 and Wayne Parnell for nought in the same over.
Stephan Myburgh scored 37 runs for the Netherlands.
Netherlands scored 31 runs from the final two overs with contributions from Colin Ackermann and Scott Edwards.
Post-Match Reflections: South Africa skipper Temba Bavuma expressed disappointment, stating they had confidence and belief to make the play-offs but lost wickets at crucial times.
Dutch skipper Scott Edwards expressed being 'lost for words' and called it another big upset for Netherlands in a World Cup.
Colin Ackermann felt fantastic about the victory, stating the team worked really hard and deserved the win.
Miscellaneous Highlights: South Africa was eliminated from the World Cup despite being undefeated after three games.
The result left Bangladesh and Pakistan fighting for the final spot in the last four.
India topped the group and played Zimbabwe in the final match of the day to decide the final Super 12 standings.
